<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="96" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="96">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="96">
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Parker" authorityYear="1929" class="Hexapoda" family="Crabronidae" genus="Bembix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="regnata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="96">Bembix regnata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described by Parker from two localities in Tanganyika (Usaramo and Rufiaji Klurtusteppe) and Nyasa [Malawi] (Lake Nyasa). Arnold described his 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Arnold" authorityYear="1929" class="Hexapoda" family="Crabronidae" genus="Bembix" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="96" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="speciosa">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="96">Bembix speciosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Southern Rhodesia [Zimbabwe] (Gwaai, Victoria Falls, Matopos, Sanyati Valley and Bulawayo).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
