<subSubSection pageId="43" pageNumber="96" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="96">Geographical distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="43" pageNumber="96">
From north to south Zimbawe, in South Africa known from one specimen from northern coastal KwaZulu-Natal (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Distributions of collection records of Bembix spp.: a Bembix namibensis b Bembix ochracea c Bembix olivata d Bembix regnata e Bembix scaura f Bembix sibilans." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/11863" pageId="43" pageNumber="96">Fig. 14d</figureCitation>
). Further records are required to establish a distribution pattern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
